Installing The Frood
====================

*Author* [Jens Riisom Schultz](mailto:jers@fynskemedier.dk)
*Since*  2011-06-21

To set a module up for The Frood, you need to create two `.htaccess`-files and two `index.php` files.


Add The Frood as an external
----------------------------

From the command line:

	cd /the/root/of/the/module
	mkdir lib
	svn propedit svn:externals lib

Add the following line:

	frood svn://develop.fyens.dk/frood/tags/latest/src

Save, quit and:

	svn up


The admin interface
-------------------

Edit `admin/.htaccess` (Change `moduleName` to the actual dirname of the module):

	RewriteEngine on

	# You need to change this to the correct module name
	RewriteBase /modules/moduleName/admin/

	# These rules exclude real files and directories from
	# the rewriting and lets them pass through unaffected
	RewriteCond %{REQUEST_FILENAME} !-f
	RewriteCond %{REQUEST_FILENAME} !-d

	# Direct all requests to lib/frood/run/admin.php, except specified file types
	RewriteRule !\.(js|ico|txt|gif|jpg|png|css)$ ../lib/frood/run/admin.php


The public part
---------------

Edit `.htaccess` (Change `moduleName` to the actual dirname of the module):

	RewriteEngine on

	# You need to change this to the correct module name
	RewriteBase /modules/moduleName/

	# These rules exclude real files and directories from
	# the rewriting and lets them pass through unaffected
	RewriteCond %{REQUEST_FILENAME} !-f
	RewriteCond %{REQUEST_FILENAME} !-d

	# Direct all requests to lib/frood/run/public.php, except specified file types
	RewriteRule !\.(js|ico|txt|gif|jpg|png|css)$ lib/frood/run/public.php


*That's it.*